============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Law of Large Numbers
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      Sample mean converges to expected value
Applications: Insurance, gambling, statistics
Discoverer:   Jacob Bernoulli (1713)

Theorem/Law:  Fundamental Theorem of Calculus
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      ∫[a,b] f'(x)dx = f(b) - f(a)
Applications: Physics, engineering, economics
Discoverer:   Newton/Leibniz (1670)

Theorem/Law:  Pythagorean Theorem
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      a² + b² = c²
Applications: Navigation, construction, computer graphics
Discoverer:   Pythagoras (500)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   The right action maximizes total happiness for greatest number
Philosopher:  Bentham/Mill
Example:      Sacrifice one to save five if it maximizes total utility

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is machine learning?
A1: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

Q2: What is gravity?
A2: Gravity is an attractive force between all masses.
     Newton described it as F = Gm1m2/r². Einstein refined
     it as spacetime curvature in general relativity.

Q3: What is plate tectonics?
A3: Earth's crust is divided into tectonic plates that move
     on the mantle. Their interactions create earthquakes,
     volcanoes, mountains, and ocean trenches over millions
     of years.

Q4: What is the speed of light?
A4: The speed of light in a vacuum is 299,792,458 meters
     per second (approximately 300,000 km/s), denoted as c.

Q5: What is the Big Bang?
A5: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

